    bibo:volume "5196" ;
    dc:creator "Freitas, Felipe V." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "New genus and subgenus of South American long-horned bees (Apidae, Eucerini)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7235829> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7235829>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Savannychapis interrupta (Urban 1989): Female (Paratypus) in a) lateral and b) frontal views; specimen from Bahia, Brazil. Male in d) dorsal and e) frontal views; specimen from Mato Grosso, Brazil. g) detail of the three-segmented maxillary palpi, and h) sterna of male, to highlight the structure of S6 with two apicolateral carinae, not converging near the midline, and with basolateral depressions. Both specimens were studied by Dr. Danuncia Urban (DZUP) and used to confirm the identity of the vouchers included in the phylogenetic study subsidizing the proposal of the new genus. Scale bars = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7235829/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

